That's what MS and Intel and the rest want you to do.

But you can't realistically expect that the latest and greatest
stuff will run on your 386.  OTOH, nobody is forcing you to buy
the new stuff either.  If it works the way it is, and you're
happy with it, one option is to cancel your computer mags, stop
reading groups like this, and get on with your life.  There is
no freshness date on software.  If it does the job, then you have
no worries.


